{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = | image = <!-- include the file, px and alt: [[File:Example.jpg|200px|alt=Cover]] --> | image_caption = | author = [[Andrew Nelson (lexicographer)|Andrew N. Nelson]] | cover_artist = | country = Japan, United States of America | language = English-Japanese | subject = Japanese-English character dictionary | publisher = C. E. Tuttle Co. | pub_date = 1962 | media_type = Print | pages = 1048 | awards = 1969 Prize for the Society for the Promotion of International Cultural Relations ''(Kokusai Bunka Shinkōkai)''<ref name="Tuttle">{{cite web | title = Publisher's web site | url = http://www.tuttlepublishing.com/book/?GCOI=48053100471140 | date = | accessdate = 28 November 2012}}</ref> | isbn = | dewey = | congress = PL679 .N4<ref>{{cite web | title = Library of Congress Catalog Record | url = http://lccn.loc.gov/61011973 | date = | accessdate = 28 November 2012}}</ref> }}
'''''{{Nihongo|The Modern Reader's Japanese-English Character Dictionary|最新漢英辞典|Saishin Kan-Ei jiten}}''''' is a [[kanji]] dictionary published with [[English language|English]] speakers in mind. Although a revised edition by John H. Haig, ''[[The New Nelson Japanese-English Character Dictionary]]'', was published in 1997, it is still in print, now under the title ''The Original Modern Reader's Japanese-English Character Dictionary – Classic Edition''<ref name="Tuttle"/>
The dictionary contains about 5,000 entries, listing characters with their ''on'' and ''kun'' readings, compounds and English definitions. The entries are arranged by a system devised by the author as an extension of the traditional [[Radical (Chinese character)|radical]] system.
